<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
      integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/styles.css" />

    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1 class="heading1">
        <div class="p-3 p-md-5 text-white rounded">
          <div class="col-md-12 px-0">
            <h1 class="display-4 fst-italic">
              Welcome To Joey's Blog Web App!
            </h1>
            <p class="lead my-3">
              Hopefully you draw a bit of inspiration from this capstone project
              website and model your blog project after. <em>Enjoy!</em> ðŸ˜ŽðŸ‘ŒðŸ”¥
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="frosted-glass">
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h2><a href="/blog/<%= showPost.id %>">Persistence.</a></h2>
            <p>by Joel Kwashie Segbefia</p>
            <p>
              Persistence is the ability to stick with something. If you
              practice the violin for over a year in order to play "Twinkle,
              Twinkle, Little Star" perfectly, that's persistence! Persistence
              can also mean something that lasts for a very long time.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <% if (locals.showPost) { %> <% showPost.forEach(showPost => { %>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h2 class="blog-post-title">
              <a href="/blog/<%= showPost.id %>"><%= showPost.title %></a>
            </h2>
            <p class="blog-post-meta">by <em><%= showPost.author %></em></p>
            <p><%= showPost.content %></p>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <% }); %> <% } %>
      </div>
      <form action="/submit" method="get">
        <div class="d-grid gap-2 col-6 mx-auto">
          <button class="btn btn-dark btn-sm" type="submit">Create Post</button>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
    <%- include("footer.ejs") %>
  </body>
</html>
